  "prompt": "Should I switch my major from economics to psychology if I want to work in HR?",
  "response": "If you want to work in HR, a psychology major can be beneficial, as it provides insights into human behavior, motivation, and organizational dynamics. However, an economics background can also be valuable in HR, especially for roles involving compensation, benefits, and organizational strategy.\n\nConsider these factors:\n1. Psychology major advantages:\n- Better understanding of workplace behavior\n- Stronger background in employee motivation\n- More direct alignment with HR principles\n\n2. Economics major advantages:\n- Strong analytical skills\n- Understanding of organizational economics\n- Data-driven decision-making abilities\n\nRecommendations:\n- Take HR-related electives in either major\n- Consider a minor in the other field\n- Look for internships in HR\n- Speak with HR professionals about their educational backgrounds\n- Consider a relevant graduate degree or HR certification\n\nUltimately, both majors can lead to successful HR careers. Your choice should depend on your specific interests and career goals.",
